[medium] policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness.rego:56 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library)
Secrets Manager rotation rules can use ScheduleExpression without AutomaticallyAfterDays; the collector normalizes a missing AutomaticallyAfterDays to 0. rotation_deadline_days then becomes 0, so any rotation with a non-empty last_rotated_date and a schedule expression such as rate(30 days) is immediately reported as rotation_overdue even when it rotated yesterday.
Suggested fix: Only evaluate the overdue rule when automatically_after_days > 0, or derive a day cadence from supported rate(...) schedule_expression values and skip with a clear skip_reason for unsupported/cron schedules. Add a test with automatically_after_days=0 and schedule_expression="rate(30 days)".
Guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness.rego, do not compute or enforce rotation_overdue when automatically_after_days is 0, null, or otherwise not a positive number. The minimal safe patch is to change rotation_deadline_days and the rotation_overdue body so the rule only evaluates when automatically_after_days > 0, then compare days_since_rotation against automatically_after_days * data.rotation_grace_multiplier. This prevents ScheduleExpression-only rotation rules, which the collector normalizes to automatically_after_days=0, from being immediately overdue. Do not try to parse cron expressions in a quick fix. Add a test in policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness_test.rego with rotation_enabled=true, last_rotated_date recent, rotation_rules={"automatically_after_days": 0, "schedule_expression": "rate(30 days)"}, and assert rotation_overdue is absent. Keep rotation_never_executed unchanged for enabled rotation with empty last_rotated_date.
