[medium] policies/secretsmanager_scheduled_deletion_window.rego:52 (correctness)
The collector defaults config.recovery_window_days to 0 and only replaces it when a matched DeleteSecret CloudTrail event exposes recoveryWindowInDays. The policy interprets recovery_window_days == 0 as force_delete_used whenever deleted_date is set, so a normally scheduled deletion is reported as force-delete if CloudTrail lookup failed, the event was not matched, or the evidence lacks the request parameter. The confidential disposal-window policy has the same assumption.
Suggested fix: Represent unknown recovery windows separately from force-delete evidence: either consume an explicit force_delete_without_recovery field from dynamic evidence, or treat 0 as unknown unless a DeleteSecret event proves ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery. Mirror the fix in the confidential disposal-window policy and add missing-CloudTrail tests.
Guidance: Fix the evidence model before relying on policy logic: recovery_window_days=0 is currently ambiguous because README/default fixtures use 0 and the collector can leave 0 when CloudTrail recoveryWindowInDays is missing. Introduce or consume an explicit boolean config.force_delete_without_recovery that is true only when matched DeleteSecret evidence proves ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery=true. Then update policies/secretsmanager_scheduled_deletion_window.rego and policies/secretsmanager_confidential_disposal_window.rego so force_delete_used requires force_delete_without_recovery == true, not recovery_window_days == 0. For recovery_window_below_minimum checks, evaluate only when recovery_window_days is not null and recovery_window_days > 0; do not report an unknown/missing recovery window as below minimum or force-delete. Update tests in both *_test.rego files: keep a positive-window below-minimum case, add an explicit force_delete_without_recovery=true case that triggers force_delete_used, and add a missing-CloudTrail/unknown case with deleted_date set and recovery_window_days either null or 0 plus no force_delete_without_recovery where force_delete_used is absent. If the collector lives outside policies/, make the corresponding field change there as part of the same fix.
